          "title": "The necessity of suffering before glory",
          "body": "Three times Luke uses *dei* (\"it is necessary\") to frame the cross-and-resurrection (24:7, 26, 44). This is not divine afterthought; it is the unalterable purpose of God revealed in the Hebrew Scriptures. The angels cite Jesus's own *dei* (v. 7); Jesus on the road rebukes the disciples for missing the *dei* (v. 26); Jesus in the upper room grounds the *dei* in Law, Prophets, and Psalms (v. 44). The chapter rules out two errors: theology that denies the necessity of the cross (the disciples' shock in vv. 19-21) and theology that denies the necessity of glory beyond the cross (a stunted Christology). Suffering and glory are *one* divine arc, prophesied and accomplished."
